					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4340296#post-3686102</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4340296/scp-3820#post-3686102</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 19 Jan 2018 06:16:55 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Tsaiah</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2210974</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Love the concept, and the dialogue makes for an A+ payoff. +1</p> <p>My one nitpick: I tend to agree that the animals themselves being anomalous or not is kind of not the point here, and probably unnecessary? It just seems outside the scope of the otherwise great little gem you've got going here.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4340296#post-3641064</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4340296/scp-3820#post-3641064</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 27 Nov 2017 19:37:04 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Bear-run</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1766089</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Thanks for the feedback!</p> <p>The animals being anomalous was just a plot element to get the Foundation involved. Though in hindsight, the animals being normal would still draw in Foundation attention if they started popping out of nowhere or suddenly demanifesting in animal shelters.</p> <p>Other than that, what do you think of the dialogue?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4340296#post-3640809</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4340296/scp-3820#post-3640809</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 27 Nov 2017 11:46:34 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MrWrong</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2039383</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I think the image used feels not very necessary. If you're gonna use the image, I think you could have afforded to show the different types of anomalous animals involved, instead of only going through with the scam idea. Indeed, the scam idea on its own can be about normal animals too.</p> <p>What would anomalous animals add to the story, beyond the superficial element of 'This makes it not normal'?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4340296#post-3640369</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4340296/scp-3820#post-3640369</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 26 Nov 2017 19:40:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Bear-run</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1766089</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Thanks for reading!</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▶&nbsp;You&nbsp;got&nbsp;it&nbsp;about&nbsp;right</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">◀&nbsp;Collapse</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>The scammers actually know of the Foundation, which is why they leave the pets on Earth, knowing that they'll be taken care of and not starve to death. That's how they were able to maintain the scheme for three years.</p> <p>Is there any way I could have made this clearer in the article?</p> <p>And what do you think of the dialogue?</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4340296#post-3640225</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4340296/scp-3820#post-3640225</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 26 Nov 2017 13:56:33 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Abettik</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1700758</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>+1</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Let's&nbsp;see&nbsp;if&nbsp;I've&nbsp;got&nbsp;this&nbsp;right...</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>So, on some other-dimensional world somewhere, there is a service that advertises itself as a pet-sitting service. They advertise things like &quot;organic sacrifices&quot; and &quot;five star accommodations.&quot; However, instead of actually taking care of the pets, they transport the pets to Earth for the duration, and then transport them back afterwards. The Foundation getting involved was either a bonus or something they forsaw&#8230; the Foundation is actually taking better care of the pets than leaving them in the &quot;wild&quot; on Earth.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
